# Git Commit Message Format

When generating commit messages, always follow this format strictly:

## Format
<Type>(<file>): <what was done>

## Types
Feat / Fix / Refactor / Perf / Style / Docs / Test / Chore

## Rules
- Output in English only
- Subject line must be under 72 characters
- Use present tense ("Add", "Fix", "Update", not "Added", "Fixed")
- No body, no footer, single line only
- <file> should be the main filename changed (without path or extension)
- Capitalize the first letter of the subject (after the colon and space)

## Examples
Fix(image_upscaler): Remove redundant pil_to_cv2 conversion in run_pipeline
Perf(image_upscaler): Release VRAM cache after GPU inference
Feat(app): Add session restore logic via URL query param
Refactor(image_upscaler): Replace random EDSR weights with bicubic interpolation